---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navigation from '../../components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="P.R.O.M.P.T Framework: Systematic Prompt Engineering"
  description="The P.R.O.M.P.T framework - Purpose, Results, Obstacles, Mindset, Preferences, Technical. A systematic methodology for effective AI interactions."
  canonical="https://snailsploit.com/frameworks/prompt"
  ogType="article"
  ogImage="/images/og-prompt.png"
  keywords={[
    'P.R.O.M.P.T framework',
    'prompt engineering methodology',
    'systematic prompting',
    'LLM interaction framework'
  ]}
>
  <Navigation slot="header" />

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6 font-mono" style="color: var(--color-accent-cyan);">
        P.R.O.M.P.T Framework
      </h1>
      <p class="text-2xl mb-4" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">
        Systematic Prompt Engineering Methodology
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Overview</h2>
        <p>
          The P.R.O.M.P.T framework provides a systematic approach to prompt engineering, ensuring
          consistent and effective interactions with AI systems. By following six key principles,
          practitioners can achieve reliable results across different models and use cases.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">The Six Principles</h2>

        <h3 style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">P - Purpose</h3>
        <p>
          Clearly define what you want to achieve. A well-defined purpose guides the entire interaction
          and helps the AI understand the context and goals.
        </p>

        <h3 style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">R - Results</h3>
        <p>
          Specify the expected output format, structure, and quality criteria. Define what success looks like.
        </p>

        <h3 style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">O - Obstacles</h3>
        <p>
          Anticipate and address potential challenges, edge cases, and failure modes in your prompt design.
        </p>

        <h3 style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">M - Mindset</h3>
        <p>
          Set the appropriate role, perspective, and cognitive approach for the AI to adopt.
        </p>

        <h3 style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">P - Preferences</h3>
        <p>
          Communicate stylistic choices, tone requirements, and output preferences.
        </p>

        <h3 style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">T - Technical</h3>
        <p>
          Include technical specifications, constraints, and requirements for the interaction.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Applications</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Security assessment and penetration testing</li>
          <li>Code generation and review</li>
          <li>Technical documentation</li>
          <li>Research and analysis</li>
          <li>Adversarial testing of AI systems</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .prose h2, .prose h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    margin-top: 1.5em;
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--color-accent-cyan);
  }
</style>
